articles.author: CBS News
articles.title: Tokyo Olympics face questions over coronavirus
articles.description: Concern has grown ahead of the summer Olympics in Japan as the number of global cases of coronavirus has climbed to over 76,000. CBS News foreign correspondent Debora Patta joined CBSN AM from Tokyo with how the outbreak might affect the Olympic Games.

articles.author: CBS News
articles.title: Latest group of Americans released from quarantine amid coronavirus outbreak
articles.description: More than 21 people have died from coronavirus, mostly in China. Now, a group of Americans evacuees, released from federal quarantine, were bussed to airports in California. Carter Evans has the latest.

articles.author: CBS News
articles.title: Officials letting last uninfected passengers leave Diamond Princess
articles.description: The quarantined cruise ship docked at Yokohama, near Tokyo, had the biggest cluster of COVID-19 cases outside China. Two passengers died.
articles.content:
Japan says a two-week quarantine of the Diamond Princess cruise ship is over, and the last passengers who tested negative for the new coronavirus are being allowed to disembark. The ship was the site of the largest outbreak of the disease outside China.

articles.author: Aimee Picchi
articles.title: Trump suggests more farm bailouts as China purchases fall short
articles.description: In an all-caps tweet, President Trump said more farm aid would be paid by tariffs, which are paid by U.S. consumers.
articles.content:
President Donald Trump hinted Friday that more farm bailouts could be on the way, "PAID FOR OUT OF THE MASSIVE TARIFF MONEY COMING INTO THE USA." 
Tariffs on imports are paid by U.S. companies and consumers, however.
